cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual speech recognition and involves video processing and deep neural networks. It may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves mapping phonemes to words. The sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SD), machine learning (cs.LG), and multimedia (cs.MM) are also possible as they are related to the development and training of the lipreading system and the processing of large amounts of video data.
